 Usage instructions

This workflow is designed to roll-back a patch from Oracle Grid Infrastructure on 11.2 and 12.1 environments. The workflow will work for both Grid Standalone and Grid
Cluster environments. In order to run on a clustered environment all that is needed it the provide the "Grid Nodes" parameter and list all nodes that
are part of the Oracle Cluster.

 Results verification

To further verify the results\:

\# Log in to the target server.
\# Set the ORACLE_HOME to your Grid Home.
\# run command\: $ORACLE_HOME/OPatch/opatch lsinventory
\# Then verify the patch number from the archive you specified is listed in the output


 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the OTHER FILES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Instance.oracle home - No description
    Instance.os user - No description
    Patch Archive - Required\: Patch Archive File of the Patch applied that you would like to rollback from GRID and your Databases.
    Server.Become Routine - No description
    Server.Name - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Download Location - Location where Archive files exists or will be downloaded to.
    Run Database View Recompile - *Optional\: Flag to indicate if Database View Recompile step should be run.
    Preparatory SQL - *Optional\: File name containing SQL statements that must be run before the database catalog update. This file is passed directly to SQLPlus and must be formatted as such. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server.
    Cleanup - Cleanup any downloaded and extracted files.
    Grid Nodes - Optional\: List of nodes part of a Grid Infrastructure environment. By default this information will be gathers via olsnodes.
    OCM Response File - *Optional\: Path name of the Oracle Configuration Manager (OCM) response file. If not found on the target, this file is downloaded from the software directory on the HP DMA server. If left blank, a default response file will be created.
    Ignorable Oracle Errors - *Optional\: A comma-separated list of Oracle errors to be ignored when applying the patch to the database. This is in addition to the list of Oracle errors specified in the patch readme. Values are of the form ORA-nnnnn. Example\: ORA-04020,ORA-03113
    Extract Location - Location where archive files will be extracted.
    Oracle Database Homes Selection - Optional\: Oracle Database Homes you would like to roll-back patch with Grid. Valid Values ALL, NONE, INCLUDE\: Comma separated list of Oracle Homes to be patched with Grid, EXCLUDE\: Comma separated list of Oracle Homes to Exclude patching process
